title: Simpsons Roasting on an Open Fire
plot: Homer is forced to become a department store Santa when Marge spends the family's Christmas savings on removing Bart's tattoo.

title: Bart the Genius
plot: Bart ends up at a school for gifted children after cheating on an IQ test.

title: Homer's Odyssey
plot: After losing his job, Homer contemplates ending it all, until he discovers a new life path as a safety advocate.

title: There's No Disgrace Like Home
plot: After being embarrassed by the rest of the family at a company picnic, Homer becomes obsessed with improving their behavior towards each other.

title: Bart the General
plot: After being beaten up by Nelson Muntz one too many times, Bart turns to Grampa for help, and soon leads a rebellion against the school bully.

title: Moaning Lisa
plot: A depressed Lisa's spirit is lifted when she meets a jazz-man, Bleeding Gums Murphy.

title: The Call of the Simpsons
plot: Homer takes the family camping, but it soon becomes a misadventure when they lose their equipment and Homer is mistaken for Bigfoot.

title: The Telltale Head
plot: Bart gets more than he bargained for when he saws the head off a statue of the town's founder.

title: Life on the Fast Lane
plot: After Homer humiliates Marge on her birthday, she takes up bowling out of spite, only to develop a mutual infatuation with a suave French instructor.

title: Homer's Night Out
plot: After a photograph of Homer gyrating with an exotic dancer is distributed throughout Springfield, he finds himself kicked out of the house by Marge.

title: The Crepes of Wrath
plot: Bart is sent to France on a student exchange program, where he's treated like a slave; an Albanian student with suspicious motives takes Bart's place in the family.

title: Krusty Gets Busted
plot: After Krusty is found guilty of robbing the Kwik-E-Mart following Homer's eyewitness testimony, Bart and Lisa set out to prove his innocence.

title: Some Enchanted Evening
plot: Homer takes Marge out for a night on the town to make up for his recent neglecting of her, leaving the kids with a sinister babysitter who has a diabolical secret.

title: Lard of the Dance
plot: Homer and Bart try to start their own grease business; Lisa organizes a school dance.

title: The Wizard of Evergreen Terrace
plot: Homer's midlife crisis leads to a disastrous attempt at being an inventor.

title: Bart the Mother
plot: When Bart accidentally kills a mother bird, he tries to make amends by raising the eggs.

title: Treehouse of Horror IX
plot: Homer receives an evil hair transplant; Bart and Lisa get trapped in an Itchy and Scratchy cartoon; Maggie is revealed to be an alien.

title: When You Dish Upon a Star
plot: Homer becomes a Hollywood insider when he befriends Alec Baldwin and Kim Basinger.

title: D'oh-in' in the Wind
plot: Homer becomes a hippie after a revelation about his middle name.

title: Lisa Gets an 'A'
plot: When Lisa cheats on a test, she has a moral crisis when her perfect score qualifies the school for grant money; Homer adopts a lobster as a pet.

title: Homer Simpson in: 'Kidney Trouble'
plot: Homer gets cold feet before a transplant operation which could save Grampa's life.

title: Mayored to the Mob
plot: Homer deals with corruption when he becomes Mayor Quimby's bodyguard.

title: Viva Ned Flanders
plot: When Homer takes Ned to Las Vegas in an attempt to get him to loosen up, the two end up drunkenly marrying a pair of cocktail waitresses.

title: Wild Barts Can't Be Broken
plot: The children of Springfield revolt after a curfew is enforced.

title: Sunday, Cruddy Sunday
plot: Homer and his friends head to the Super Bowl, but are forced to sneak in when they discover their tickets are counterfeit.

title: Homer to the Max
plot: Homer changes his name to "Max Power" after discovering that he shares his name with a dimwitted TV character.

title: I'm with Cupid
plot: The husbands of Springfield plot revenge after Apu outshines them on Valentine's Day.

title: Marge Simpson in: 'Screaming Yellow Honkers'
plot: Marge's new SUV gives her a potent case of road rage.

title: Make Room for Lisa
plot: Lisa feels that her relationship with her father will never be close, and she develops stress-induced stomach pains; Marge inadvertently knocks out Milhouse.

title: Maximum Homerdrive
plot: Homer takes Bart with him on a cross-country delivery on behalf of a trucker who died before completing it; Marge and Lisa experience problems with their new novelty doorbell.

title: Simpsons Bible Stories
plot: Three famous religious stories are retold Simpsons style as the family nods off at church.

title: Mom and Pop Art
plot: Homer becomes the talk of the Springfield art community when a failed barbecue pit he worked on is mistaken for an art project.

title: The Old Man and the 'C' Student
plot: Bart is punished with community service at the Retirement Castle after he ruins Springfield's chances of hosting the Olympics.

title: Monty Can't Buy Me Love
plot: When a wealthy man moves to Springfield, Mr. Burns begins to feel that he is losing his grasp on the citizens and decides to enlist the help of Homer.

title: They Saved Lisa's Brain
plot: Lisa is invited to join the Springfield chapter of MENSA and after Mayor Quimby flees, the group ends up running the city. Meanwhile, Homer poses for a series of erotic photos.

title: Thirty Minutes Over Tokyo
plot: The Simpsons must perform on a Japanese game show after Homer loses their money on a vacation.

title: Beyond Blunderdome
plot: Convinced he's the only man with guts to tell him the truth, Mel Gibson insists Homer accompanies him in Hollywood to help fix his newest film project.

title: Brother's Little Helper
plot: Bart is put on medication to control his behavior, but the pills cause him to become paranoid and insane.

title: Guess Who's Coming to Criticize Dinner?
plot: When Homer is hired as a local food critic by a newspaper in Springfield, he finds himself in deep trouble after his reviews turn out to be too critical.

title: Treehouse of Horror X
plot: The Simpsons attempt to cover up their accidental murder of Ned Flanders. Bart and Lisa acquire super powers. An electronic apocalypse threatens Springfield.

title: E-I-E-I-(Annoyed Grunt)
plot: Homer cowards out of a pistol-duel and hides out with the rest of the family on a country farm.

title: Hello Gutter, Hello Fadder
plot: Homer becomes a minor celebrity around Springfield after bowling a perfect game.

title: Eight Misbehavin'
plot: Apu struggles with fatherhood after Manjula gives birth to octuplets.

title: Take My Wife, Sleaze
plot: Homer's attempt at creating a motorcycle gang attracts a real gang, who kidnap Marge.

title: Grift of the Magi
plot: A toy company purchases Springfield Elementary and uses the student body as a focus group for their new Christmas toy Funzo.

title: Little Big Mom
plot: Lisa finds out how rough Marge has it when her mom is in traction and she becomes the woman of the house. Homer and Bart's antics get her so worked up she conspires to teach them a lesson.

title: Faith Off
plot: Bart is led to believe he has special healing powers after a tent revival.

title: The Mansion Family
plot: Homer receives responsibility for Mr. Burns' mansion when he is on leave and takes Burns' yacht to international waters to have a party.

title: Saddlesore Galactica
plot: The Simpsons get an abused horse and make him a contender in horse racing. Homer finds out a secret conspiracy about jockeys. Lisa tries to reach President Clinton when the results of a school band talent competition seem tainted.

title: Alone Again, Natura-Diddly
plot: Ned deals with his grief after Maude's untimely death.

title: Missionary: Impossible
plot: When Homer is wanted dead for reneging on a 10,000 dollar pledge to PBS, Reverend Lovejoy sets him up for missionary work in the South Pacific until the heat dies down.

title: Pygmoelian
plot: Plastic surgery not only transforms Moe the Bartender from ugly to hunky, it helps gets him a job on a hit daytime drama.

title: Bart to the Future
plot: Bart gets a glimpse of the future while the family is on vacation at an Indian casino.

title: Days of Wine and D'oh'ses
plot: Homer doesn't like it when Barney quits drinking; Bart and Lisa get into trouble when they enter a photo contest for the new phone book cover.

title: Kill the Alligator and Run
plot: Fearing he only has three years to live, Homer takes the family on a vacation to Florida, where they become fugitives after seemingly killing a famous alligator.

title: Last Tap Dance in Springfield
plot: Lisa has difficulties learning to tap dance; Bart and Milhouse ditch summer camp to spend a week living in the mall.

title: It's a Mad, Mad, Mad, Mad Marge
plot: Everybody loves the new Simpsons' house guest Becky. Except Marge, who thinks Becky wants to kill her.

title: Behind the Laughter
plot: Fans are invited to take a behind-the-scenes look at "The Simpsons," revisiting some of the most memorable experiences the family has been through.

title: Treehouse of Horror XI
plot: Homer must do one good deed to get into Heaven; Bart and Lisa encounter a witch in a gingerbread house; Super-intelligent dolphins strike back at humanity.

title: A Tale of Two Springfields
plot: Springfield is split in two when Homer revolts because his area code is changed; the new town walls itself off from the neighbors.

title: Insane Clown Poppy
plot: After he learns he has a daughter, Krusty turns to Homer for parenting advice.

title: Lisa the Treehugger
plot: Lisa's crush on an environmental activist inspires her to live in a tree threatened by loggers.

title: Homer vs. Dignity
plot: Desperate for money, Homer accepts payment from Mr. Burns in exchange for humiliating himself.

title: The Computer Wore Menace Shoes
plot: Homer's gossip website becomes a huge hit, but when his information runs out he resorts to making up news.

title: The Great Money Caper
plot: The whole town of Springfield conspires to teach Homer and Bart a lesson after the pair begin running confidence scams.

title: Skinner's Sense of Snow
plot: A freak blizzard traps the students of Springfield Elementary inside their school. Their lives at stake, they are at the mercy of the rescue efforts of a woozy Homer and Ned.

title: HOMR
plot: An X-ray reveals a crayon lodged in Homer's brain. After the crayon is removed, Homer experiences a sudden surge in intelligence, making him closer to Lisa and isolated from his friends.

title: Pokey Mom
plot: Marge befriends a convict with an artistic streak. Meanwhile, Homer battles the chiropractic industry after he creates a miracle back pain cure.

title: Worst Episode Ever
plot: Bart and Milhouse are left in charge of the comic book store after Comic Book Guy is hospitalized.

title: Tennis the Menace
plot: Homer installs a tennis court in the backyard, but his lousy playing creates a rift in the family.

title: Day of the Jackanapes
plot: When Krusty decides to retire after a new game show draws away his audience, a vengeful Sideshow Bob plots to have a hypnotized Bart assassinate him during his farewell special.

title: New Kids on the Blecch
plot: A music producer offers Bart and his friends a chance to participate in an up-and-coming boyband, but the boys are not up to it after making a discovery.

title: Hungry Hungry Homer
plot: Homer is forced to go on a hunger strike by the Springfield Isotopes after uncovering a secret plan to have the baseball team moved to New Mexico.

title: Bye Bye Nerdy
plot: Problems with a bully lead Lisa to examine just what makes bullies aggressive. Meanwhile, Homer gets into the baby-proofing business.

title: Simpson Safari
plot: The Simpsons win a trip to Africa after Homer finds a golden animal cracker from the 60's in the loft.

title: Trilogy of Error
plot: Homer's rush to the hospital to re-attach his severed thumb, Lisa's rush to school to win the science fair, and Bart's run-in with an illegal fireworks scheme interconnect from their point of view.

title: I'm Goin' to Praiseland
plot: With Homer's help, Flanders tries to establish a Christian theme park based on drawings in Maude's sketch book.

title: Children of a Lesser Clod
plot: After a debilitating injury forces him to stay indoors, Homer begins a daycare center.

title: Simpsons Tall Tales
plot: A hobo tells the Simpsons tall tales on a train ride:. In the first story, Homer is Paul Bunyan. In the second, Lisa stars as Connie Appleseed. And in the third, Bart and Nelson raft down the Mississippi as Tom Sawyer and Huck Finn.

title: Treehouse of Horror XII
plot: A gypsy puts a curse on Homer; The Simpsons' new automated house malfunctions and tries to kill Homer; Bart and Lisa attend a school for wizards.

title: The Parent Rap
plot: After Bart takes a joyride in a police car, a judge orders him to be tethered to Homer at all times.

title: Homer the Moe
plot: Homer and his friends are forced to drink in the Simpsons' garage after Moe the Bartender renovates his shady bar into a hipster hangout.

title: A Hunka Hunka Burns in Love
plot: Mr. Burns falls in love with a younger woman and recruits Homer to help him impress her.

title: The Blunder Years
plot: A hypnotist uncovers a traumatic experience from Homer's childhood that he had sealed away for years. What exactly happened, and what hand does Mr Burns have in all this?

title: She of Little Faith
plot: Homer and Bart get careless with a model rocket and accidentally do damage to Springfield's church, but when Mr. Burns offers to commercialize it to repair the destruction, Lisa leaves Christianity behind to become a Buddhist.

title: Brawl in the Family
plot: A social services officer brings unity to the Simpson family, but their newfound happiness is threatened when the cocktail waitress Homer married in Vegas shows up at their door.

title: Sweets and Sour Marge
plot: Marge rallies for a ban on sugar after Springfield is declared America's fattest city.

title: Jaws Wired Shut
plot: Marge can't deal with the quiet after Homer has his jaws wired shut.

title: Half-Decent Proposal
plot: Marge's high school sweetheart Artie Ziff returns and offers Homer a million dollars to spend a weekend with Marge.

title: The Bart Wants What It Wants
plot: Bart breaks up with his new girlfriend Greta, but gets jealous when she begins dating Milhouse.

title: The Lastest Gun in the West
plot: Bart meets a retired cowboy movie star and convinces him to make a comeback on The Krusty the Clown Show.

title: The Old Man and the Key
plot: Abe gets his driver's license back to impress a new woman at the retirement home.

title: Tales from the Public Domain
plot: Homer reads three stories from an overdue library book, imagining himself as Odysseus, Lisa as Joan of Arc, and Bart as Hamlet.

title: Blame It on Lisa
plot: Lisa sponsors an orphan in Brazil, and when he goes missing she convinces the family to go to Brazil to find him. While there, Homer is kidnapped.

title: Weekend at Burnsie's
plot: After a traumatizing eye injury, Homer becomes a habitual user of medical marijuana.

title: Gump Roast
plot: In this clip show, the citizens of Springfield honor Homer Simpsons with a Roast, but the festivities take a turn for the worst when aliens crash it.

title: I Am Furious Yellow
plot: Bart's comic about Homer becomes a hit on-line, prompting Homer to attempt to control his anger.

title: The Sweetest Apu
plot: Apu's marriage is on the rocks after Manjula finds out he cheated on her.

title: Little Girl in the Big Ten
plot: Lisa pretends to be a college student when she befriends two college girls; Bart is forced to live in a plastic bubble after being bitten by a mosquito.

title: The Frying Game
plot: Homer and Marge find themselves on death row after they are framed for murder.

title: Papa's Got a Brand New Badge
plot: Homer becomes chief of police after a scandal forces Wiggum out.

title: Treehouse of Horror XIII
plot: Homer clones himself with a magic hammock; Zombie cowboys come back from the dead after Springfield bans guns; The Simpsons family take a vacation on an island where Dr. Hibbert can turn people into animals.

title: How I Spent My Strummer Vacation
plot: When Homer is secretly videotaped complaining about his family in a taxi, they send him off to a rock and roll fantasy camp so he can try to live his dream.

title: Bart vs. Lisa vs. 3rd Grade
plot: Bart and Lisa are respectively held back and moved forward one grade, putting them in the same class.

title: Large Marge
plot: Marge accidentally gets breast implants.

title: Helter Shelter
plot: The Simpsons family must participate in a reality television show in which they try to live in the same way that the families did in the 1800s.

title: The Great Louse Detective
plot: Homer survives an assassination attempt and the police struggle to find a lead. Who is the only person in Springfield with cunning to help them crack the case? Sideshow Bob.

title: Special Edna
plot: After Skinner once again has let Mrs. Krabappel down, Bart nominates her for Teacher of the Year. When the nomination is accepted, Skinner tries to get back Krabappel by asking her to marry him.

title: The Dad Who Knew Too Little
plot: Homer hires a private detective to learn more about Lisa.

title: The Strong Arms of the Ma
plot: Marge takes up body-building to boost her self-esteem after being mugged at the Kwik-E-Mart.

title: Pray Anything
plot: Homer turns to religion to help him get what he wants and is soon awarded the church in an injury settlement. He then turns the church into his personal party pad and Reverend Lovejoy leaves Springfield to wallow in its hedonism.

title: Barting Over
plot: After finding out Homer squandered his money from a baby commercial, Bart moves out into a loft, and meets skateboarding legend Tony Hawk.

title: I'm Spelling as Fast as I Can
plot: Lisa participates in the Spellympics, but Homer is busy traveling cross-country as Krusty Burger test-markets a new sandwich. Lisa is confident that she will win, until she learns that the contest is rigged against her.

title: A Star Is Born Again
plot: Ned Flanders starts dating a famous movie star, but has difficulties with the tabloids following them everywhere.

title: Mr. Spritz Goes to Washington
plot: The family makes Krusty run for Congress because of air traffic being redirected to fly dangerously close to their house.

title: C.E.D'oh
plot: Homer takes over the power plant after tricking Mr. Burns into making him the official owner of the power plant.

title: 'Scuse Me While I Miss the Sky
plot: Lisa becomes interested in astronomy and starts fighting the light pollution which is preventing her from being able to enjoy her new hobby.

title: Three Gays of the Condo
plot: When Homer finds an old note revealing Marge only married him because she was pregnant with Bart, he moves into a condo with two gay guys.

title: Dude, Where's My Ranch?
plot: Homer writes a Christmas carol called "Everybody Hates Ned Flanders," which soon becomes so popular that the family decides to leave town for a while.

title: Old Yeller-Belly
plot: Homer throws out Santa's Little Helper for not saving him from a fire, but soon the dog becomes Duff's new mascot.

title: Brake My Wife, Please
plot: Because of Homer losing his driver's license, Marge has to drive everyone everywhere, which is so stressful for her that she accidentally runs over Homer leading to the two seeing a marriage counselor.

title: The Bart of War
plot: Bart and Milhouse are forced into community service after destroying Flanders' memorial and join separate community groups, pitting themselves against each other.

title: Moe Baby Blues
plot: After saving Maggie's life, Moe develops a special bond with her, much to Homer's dismay.

title: Treehouse of Horror XIV
plot: Homer gets a new job, as the Grim Reaper. Professor Frink brings back his father from beyond the grave, and Bart and Milhouse freeze time.

title: My Mother the Carjacker
plot: Homer's mother returns to Springfield, and the city pardons her from the charges against her. Mr. Burns is furious about this and makes a plan to get Mona Simpson in prison.

title: The President Wore Pearls
plot: Lisa feuds with Principal Skinner after being elected school president.

title: The Regina Monologues
plot: Prime minister Tony Blair welcomes the Simpsons to England where they run into author J.K. Rowling and actor Ian McKellen.

title: The Fat and the Furriest
plot: At the dump Homer is videotaped while being attacked by a bear. The town regards him a coward, so Homer decides to strike back at the bear.

title: Today, I Am a Clown
plot: Krusty decides to do what he never did when he was thirteen years old - have a Bar Mitzvah.

title: 'Tis the Fifteenth Season
plot: After spending all his money on an expensive gift for himself, and the family thinking he should be less of an egoist, Homer decides to change his ways.

title: Marge vs. Singles, Seniors, Childless Couples and Teens and Gays
plot: A concert for babies ends in a riot, so the childless adults of Springfield gather to make the town less child-friendly.

title: I, (Annoyed Grunt)-Bot
plot: Homer pretends to be a robot and competes in Robot Wars to win Bart's affection; Lisa has cat trouble.

title: Diatribe of a Mad Housewife
plot: Marge is inspired to write a novel, but the storyline of the book (a fat, mean husband, and a handsome, sweet neighbor) makes Homer jealous.

title: Margical History Tour
plot: Marge tells Lisa, Bart and Millhouse three history stories because the library doesn't have any.

title: Milhouse Doesn't Live Here Anymore
plot: Milhouse moves to Capitol City, and therefore Lisa and Bart become best friends.

title: Smart & Smarter
plot: When Maggie is revealed to have an IQ of 167, Lisa is no longer the genius of the family, causing a rivalry between the sisters.

title: The Ziff Who Came to Dinner
plot: Artie Ziff is discovered hiding out in the Simpsons' attic.

title: Co-Dependent's Day
plot: Marge takes up heavy drinking to spend more time with Homer. Bart and Lisa confront a famous movie director about the drop in quality his films have taken.

title: The Wandering Juvie
plot: After playing a prank on the whole town, Bart is sentenced to six months of juvenile detention. There he meets Gina, who forces Bart to escape with her.

title: My Big Fat Geek Wedding
plot: Mrs. Krabapel falls for Comic Book Guy and they plan a Star Trek like wedding. Principal Skinner plans to prevent it.

title: Catch 'Em If You Can
plot: Homer and Marge try to have a vacation without the kids but Bart and Lisa follow them everywhere they go.

title: Simple Simpson
plot: Homer becomes a costumed vigilante who uses pies for weapons after witnessing Lisa get humiliated at a competition at the state fair.

title: The Way We Weren't
plot: Marge and Homer find out that they actually kissed each other at age 10 without knowing they were each other's first kisses, and tell the story about this.

title: Bart-Mangled Banner
plot: An accidental photo showing Bart mooning the American flag makes the Simpsons the most hated family in town.

title: Fraudcast News
plot: After Mr. Burns is erroneously reported as dead, he buys all of he media outlets in order to prevent them from writing scathing articles about him.

title: Treehouse of Horror XV
plot: Ned gains the power to foresee people's deaths; Maggie is shrunk inside a vitamin capsule and swallowed; Eliza Simpson and her sidekick hunt down a murderer.

title: All's Fair in Oven War
plot: Homer buys Marge a new kitchen, and Marge likes cooking in the new kitchen so much she attends the Ovenfresh Bakeoff.

title: Sleeping with the Enemy
plot: Because she thinks her own children do not appreciate her anymore, Marge becomes a mother figure for Nelson.

title: She Used to Be My Girl
plot: Marge becomes jealous when Lisa begins idolizing her old high school friend, Chloe Talbot, a famous reporter.

title: Fat Man and Little Boy
plot: Bart begins designing T-shirt slogans, and his T-shirts become very popular among the citizens of Springfield.

title: Midnight Rx
plot: Homer goes to Canada with Apu and Ned to purchase Grampa's medication, but the three have problems getting home because the border guard thinks Apu is a terrorist.

title: Mommie Beerest
plot: Homer gives Moe an enormous amount of money so he doesn't have to close down.

title: Homer and Ned's Hail Mary Pass
plot: A video of Homer dancing becomes so popular that all major sports players hires Homer to design celebration dances for them.

title: Pranksta Rap
plot: Bart went to a rap concert Marge told him not to go to. In order to avoid punishment from Marge, he makes Marge and Homer believe he has been kidnapped.

title: There's Something About Marrying
plot: A townsperson comes out of the closet when Springfield legalized same-sex marriages in a plot to bolster tourism; Homer uses the Internet to become a minister.

title: On a Clear Day I Can't See My Sister
plot: After bullying her, Bart is restricted by court order to not come too close to Lisa.

title: Goo Goo Gai Pan
plot: Selma decides to adopt a child, so the whole family goes to China.

title: Mobile Homer
plot: After a garage-cleaning accident, Marge wants Homer to get life insurance. Instead, the family gets an RV.

title: The Seven-Beer Snitch
plot: Springfield builds an opera house, but since no-one attends it they convert it into a prison. Old and forgotten laws are used to fill the prison, and therefore Homer goes to jail for kicking a can five times in a row. In jail, Homer becomes a snitch

title: Future-Drama
plot: Bart and Lisa see into the future where their lives have changed.

title: Don't Fear the Roofer
plot: Homer meets a new friend, Ray the Roofer, but gets confined to a mental institution when his friends and family think he made him up.

title: The Heartbroke Kid
plot: Bart starts living on food from the new candy machine in school only, but he becomes so overweight that he has to go to a fat camp.

title: A Star Is Torn
plot: Lisa attends a singing competition for children, and Homer becomes her manager because of his skill to write songs that the crowd loves.

title: Thank God It's Doomsday
plot: Homer hears about the Rapture, and by using numerology to calculate when the Rapture is coming he learns that it is only one week away.

title: Home Away from Homer
plot: After Homer humiliates Ned Flanders, Ned, Rod, and Todd decides to leave Springfield and live in Humbleton, Pennsylvania.

title: The Father, the Son, and the Holy Guest Star
plot: Bart is expelled from Springfield Elementary, and Bart is therefore enrolled in St. Jerome's Catholic School.

title: The Bonfire of the Manatees
plot: When Marge leaves Homer because he allowed an adult movie being shot in their house, she seeks self-fulfillment in protecting manatees.

title: The Girl Who Slept Too Little
plot: A new cemetery right outside the window of Lisa's room makes Lisa suffer from many sleepless nights.

title: Milhouse of Sand and Fog
plot: When Kirk and Luann van Houten plan to get back together, Milhouse realizes they are too interested in each other, so he and Bart try to break them up, only for the plan to backfire and cause Homer and Marge to break up yet again.

title: Treehouse of Horror XVI
plot: An android son replaces Bart; Homer and friends are the quarry in Mr. Burns' hunting tournament; a witch turns townsfolk into their Halloween costumes.

title: Marge's Son Poisoning
plot: Marge and Bart start spending more time together, and make a tradition of cycling to a tea house in a small village outside Springfield.

title: See Homer Run
plot: When a recall election puts Mayor Quimby's job up for grabs, Homer seizes the opportunity to win office and gain his daughter's love.

title: The Last of the Red Hat Mamas
plot: Milhouse tutors Lisa in Italian, and Marge joins the Cheery Red Tomatoes, a group that plans to rob Mr. Burns of one million dollars worth of Faberg eggs.

title: The Italian Bob
plot: The Simpsons become lost in Italy, finding their way to a small town that Sideshow Bob has become the mayor of.

title: Simpsons Christmas Stories
plot: Homer tells the tale of the first Christmas ever, while Grandpa pursues his decade-old feud with Santa.

title: Homer's Paternity Coot
plot: When a frozen mailman from the 60's is found in a Springfield glacier, doubts arise about whether Abe really is Homer's father.

title: We're on the Road to D'ohwhere
plot: When Homer is on his way to Vegas to meet up with his friends, he has to make a detour to take Bart to an education camp. Meanwhile, Marge has discovered a surprising source of income.

title: My Fair Laddy
plot: Bart and Lisa bet whether Lisa can turn Groundskeeper Willie into a proper gentleman.

title: The Seemingly Never-Ending Story
plot: In this story within a story within a story within a story, a cave-exploring expedition, an angry sheep and a lovestruck Moe become inextricably entwined.

title: Bart Has Two Mommies
plot: Marge starts babysitting the Flanders boys, leading Homer to spend more time with Bart and Lisa. Bart gets kidnapped by a lonely movie chimpanzee.

title: Homer Simpson, This Is Your Wife
plot: As part of a new Fox show, the Simpsons participate in a wife-swap.

title: Million Dollar Abie
plot: After blowing Springfield's chances for an NFL franchise, Grandpa goes to an assisted-suicide center, then becomes a bullfighter.

title: Kiss Kiss, Bang Bangalore
plot: Homer gets sent to India when the power plant is relocated there. Selma and Patty kidnap Richard Dean Anderson after he spurns their MacGyver fan club.

title: The Wettest Stories Ever Told
plot: While waiting for the dinner at the Frying Dutchman, the family starts telling three stories about ships: "Journey on the Mayflower", "Mutiny on the Bounty", and "The Neptune Adventure".

title: Girls Just Want to Have Sums
plot: Springfield Elementary is divided into two separate schools (one for boys, one for girls) following Principal Skinner's demotion. Concerned that the boys are receiving a higher standard of education, Lisa disguises herself as a boy.

title: Regarding Margie
plot: After hitting her head on a stool Marge suffers from amnesia. Slowly but surely memories are starting to come back, except memories about Homer.

title: The Monkey Suit
plot: After his sons see a pro-evolution exhibit at a museum, Flanders demands Springfield Elementary teaches Creationism in its place, but Lisa fights for evolution lessons to be reinstated.

title: Homer and Marge Turn a Couple Play
plot: Marge and Homer try their luck at celebrity marriage counselling.

title: The Mook, the Chef, the Wife and Her Homer
plot: When Fat Tony has to take a time-out due to a whacking attempt, Homer and Bart take over the business.

title: Jazzy & The Pussycats
plot: Lisa becomes depressed when Bart becomes a better jazz musician than her. So she decides to set up an animal shelter in the Simpsons' attic.

title: Please Homer, Don't Hammer 'Em
plot: Marge begins her own carpentry business, but Homer becomes the face of the business because nobody will take a female carpenter seriously. And Bart uses Principal Skinner's peanut allergy to his advantage.

title: Treehouse of Horror XVII
plot: A meteorite turns Homer into a rampaging blob with a voracious appetite; Bart brings a Golem to life; an alien invasion hoax turns real.

title: G.I. (Annoyed Grunt)
plot: Homer is duped into signing up for the Army, and his hijinks after basic training ultimately results in a military occupation of Springfield.

title: Moe'N'a Lisa
plot: Lisa helps Moe become a distinguished poet, but she turns on him when he takes all the credit for his newfound greatness.

title: Ice Cream of Margie (with the Light Blue Hair)
plot: Homer becomes an ice cream man after being fired from the plant, and Marge uses his leftover Popsicle sticks to create folk art figures.

title: The Haw-Hawed Couple
plot: Bart and Nelson become best friends, but Bart surprisingly discovers that the fringe benefits aren't worth Nelson's neediness.

title: Kill Gil, Vol. 1 & 2
plot: The Simpsons let Gil stay with them during Christmas. However, he stays for 11 months because Marge can't tell him "no."

title: The Wife Aquatic
plot: Homer returns Marge to Barnacle Bay, where she spent her beloved summer vacations. But when they get there, they discover that it is no longer a tourist spot.

title: Revenge Is a Dish Best Served Three Times
plot: While Homer tries to get revenge on a driver who cut him off, his family warns him of the folly of revenge by telling stories based on "The Count of Monte Cristo," "Revenge of the Nerds," and "Batman."

title: Little Big Girl
plot: Lisa embellishes her family heritage as Native American for a school project; Bart gets a driver's license and develops a relationship with an older girl.

title: Springfield Up
plot: A parody of the "Up Series" of British documentaries, in which a filmmaker follows Homer and his friends from grade school into their 40s.

title: Yokel Chords
plot: In this parody of The Sound of Music (1965), Lisa becomes a tutor for Cletus' seven children, until Krusty tries to exploit them as entertainers. Meanwhile, Bart becomes emotionally attached to his school-appointed psychiatrist.

title: Rome-old and Juli-eh
plot: Homer and Patty object to Grampa and Selma's marriage; Bart and Lisa build an elaborate fort out of ill-gotten cardboard boxes.

title: Homerazzi
plot: Homer becomes a successful Paparazzi, but Springfield's celebrities decide to get their revenge on him.

title: Marge Gamer
plot: Marge decides to find out what their Internet has to offer and soon gets hooked on an online role-playing game; Homer referees Lisa's soccer game.

title: The Boys of Bummer
plot: Bart becomes the most hated person in Springfield after he is the goat in a championship baseball game, and Homer's new job as a mattress salesman ruins his and Marge's sex life.

title: Crook and Ladder
plot: Homer, Moe, Apu and Principal Skinner become volunteer firefighters. But just because they're not getting paid doesn't mean that they can't find a way to receive compensation.

title: Stop, or My Dog Will Shoot!
plot: Homer unwittingly drags the family into a cornfield maze after attempting to leave a boring Harvest fest that Marge brought them to. When everyone except Homer escapes, Santa's Little Helper rescues him and becomes the town hero. So the Simpsons enroll him in Police Dog Academy where he's teamed with Lou.

title: 24 Minutes
plot: Bart and Lisa join forces to stop the school bullies from setting off a stink bomb at the school bake sale.

title: You Kent Always Say What You Want
plot: After Kent Brockman is fired as a news anchor, he and Lisa use the Internet to expose the Fox News Conspiracy.

title: He Loves to Fly and He D'ohs
plot: Homer falls in love with private planes after taking a flight to Chicago with Mr. Burns. So Marge hires Homer a "life manager" to help him think positively and find a job that will allow him to fly for a living.

title: Homer of Seville
plot: Homer becomes an opera star after an injury improves his singing voice. His newfound popularity forces him to hire a personal assistant, who turns out to be an obsessed stalker.

title: Midnight Towboy
plot: Homer becomes the most hated man in town after he becomes a tow truck driver, and Marge teaches Maggie to not be an over-dependent baby.

title: I Don't Wanna Know Why the Caged Bird Sings
plot: Marge promises to visit a convicted bank robber in prison, but is afraid to follow through. But when the convict escapes from prison, Marge is the first person he pays a visit to.

title: Treehouse of Horror XVIII
plot: The eighteenth Simpsons Halloween Special features parodies of the movies "E.T." and "Mr. and Mrs. Smith."

title: Little Orphan Millie
plot: Milhouse's parents are lost at sea, which causes him to become a troubled loner. But his new persona makes him the new most popular kid at school, which sparks jealousy in Bart.

title: Husbands and Knives
plot: When Marge becomes a successful businesswoman, Homer becomes worried that she will dump him for a trophy husband. Therefore, he decides to have plastic surgery to make himself look like a hunk.

title: Funeral for a Fiend
plot: Bart is responsible for Sideshow Bob's death after his latest attempt at revenge is foiled, but is his death actually part of the plan?

title: Eternal Moonshine of the Simpson Mind
plot: Homer goes to Dr. Frink to help him recover his memories from the night before, and he discovers, based on his interpretation of the memories, that Marge is having an affair.

title: E Pluribus Wiggum
plot: Springfield becomes the site of the first presidential primary. The townspeople soon get sick of all of the presidential candidates sucking up to them, and decide to support their own write-in candidate: Ralph Wiggum.

title: That '90s Show
plot: Homer and Marge tell the kids about their life in the early 1990s before they were born, when Marge was enrolled in Springfield College and Homer was the lead singer of a grunge rock band.

title: Love, Springfieldian Style
plot: A series of romantic Valentine's Day parodies based on "Bonnie and Clyde," "Lady and the Tramp," and "Sid and Nancy."

title: The DeBarted
plot: The new prankster in Bart's fourth grade class actually turns out to be a mole brought in by Principal Skinner to infiltrate Bart's inner circle. Homer falls in love with his loaner car after Marge wrecks their old one.

title: Dial 'N' for Nerder
plot: One of Bart's pranks results in Martin's death, but Lisa doesn't want him to confess because she would be considered an accomplice. Marge hires a television crew to find out if Homer is cheating on his diet.

title: Smoke on the Daughter
plot: Marge has Lisa take up ballet, mainly to have Lisa live out her own childhood dreams. Lisa then succumbs to peer pressure from her ballet mates and takes up smoking. Meanwhile, Homer and Bart try to start their own beef jerky business.

title: Papa Don't Leech
plot: When the Simpsons discover that Lurleen Lumpkin is on the skids, Marge reluctantly agrees to take her in and help her find her deadbeat dad who abandoned her 30 years ago.

title: Apocalypse Cow
plot: Bart tries to save the cow he raised for his 4-H club from the slaughterhouse, and in the process winds up getting accidentally engaged to one of Cletus's daughters.

title: Any Given Sundance
plot: Lisa's documentary about her family is accepted into the Sundance Film Festival. However, her family gets upset with her when they discover that the film is far from flattering.

title: Mona Leaves-a
plot: Homer's mom dies, and as part of her will, she asks him to spread her ashes. However, her request turns out to be part of her final act of rebellion against the system.

title: All About Lisa
plot: In a parody of "All About Eve," Lisa stabs Krusty in the back, takes his job, and wins a prestigious award. Meanwhile, Homer and Bart take up coin collecting.

title: Bart Gets an F
plot: Mrs. Krabappel, fed up with Bart's lackadaisical approach to his studies, gives him an ultimatum: shape up or repeat the fourth grade.

title: Simpson and Delilah
plot: Homer lies on a medical insurance form in order to obtain a miracle hair restoring drug.

title: Treehouse of Horror
plot: The Simpsons move into a cursed house, then are abducted by aliens, before Homer is ensconced in a tale by Edgar Allen Poe.

title: Two Cars in Every Garage and Three Eyes on Every Fish
plot: After the power plant experiences bad publicity and is threatened with closure, Mr. Burns decides to run for Governor in order to have power over the law.

title: Dancin' Homer
plot: Homer's heckling of the Springfield Isotopes baseball team during one of their games inadvertently leads to his appointment as the new team mascot.

title: Dead Putting Society
plot: In an attempt to show up Ned Flanders, Homer pits Bart against Ned's son, Todd, in a miniature golf competition.

title: Bart vs. Thanksgiving
plot: On Thanksgiving, Bart runs away after refusing to apologize to a distraught Lisa for accidentally destroying her cornucopia.

title: Bart the Daredevil
plot: After seeing a motorcycle daredevil at a monster truck show, Bart becomes a death-defying daredevil skateboarder.

title: Itchy & Scratchy & Marge
plot: Marge becomes a crusader against cartoon violence after an episode of "Itchy and Scratchy" seemingly inspires Maggie to attack Homer.

title: Bart Gets Hit by a Car
plot: After Bart gets hit by a car driven by Mr. Burns, Homer is manipulated by ambulance-chaser Lionel Hutz into bringing an outrageous lawsuit against his boss.

title: One Fish, Two Fish, Blowfish, Blue Fish
plot: After apparently consuming poison blowfish, Homer is told that he only has 24 hours to live and sets to tie up all the loose threads in his life in one day.

title: The Way We Was
plot: Homer and Marge tell the story of how they met and fell in love in high school.

title: Homer vs. Lisa and the 8th Commandment
plot: Homer gets a crooked cable guy to install free cable in the Simpson home, and as a result, Lisa faces an ethical crisis over her family's stealing.

title: Principal Charming
plot: Homer tries to set Selma up with Principal Skinner, only for him to fall for Patty instead.

title: Oh Brother, Where Art Thou?
plot: Homer meets his half-brother Herb Powell, an automobile tycoon who zealously bonds with the family and tasks Homer with designing a car for the average American.

title: Bart's Dog Gets an F
plot: After an uncontrollable Santa's Little Helper destroys several important Simpson possessions, Homer announces that he will be thrown out of the house unless he completes obedience training.

title: Old Money
plot: After Grampa's new girlfriend dies and leaves him $106,000 in her will, he tries to decide what to do with it.

title: Brush with Greatness
plot: After rekindling her artistic talents, Marge is commissioned to paint a portrait of Mr. Burns; Homer vows to lose weight after getting trapped in a water slide.

title: Lisa's Substitute
plot: Lisa has a crush on her substitute teacher; Bart decides to run for class president.

title: The War of the Simpsons
plot: Homer must decide whether he should complete marriage counseling or skip out to catch a legendary catfish; Bart and Lisa take advantage of Grampa's ignorance of the house rules.

title: Three Men and a Comic Book
plot: Bart, Milhouse and Martin each pitch in to buy an highly-collectible "Radioactive Man" comic book, which soon has a disastrous effect on their friendship.

title: Blood Feud
plot: After Bart saves Mr. Burns' life with a donated blood transfusion, Homer vows revenge when they receive only a "thank you" card as compensation.

title: Sex, Pies and Idiot Scrapes
plot: Homer and Ned go into business together as bounty hunters, and Marge takes a job at an erotic bakery.

title: Lost Verizon
plot: Bart gets in trouble with Marge after she finds out that he has Denis Leary's cell phone and is using it to make prank phone calls.

title: Double, Double, Boy in Trouble
plot: Bart trades lives with his multi-millionaire lookalike, but discovers that his lookalike's life isn't all he thought it would be.

title: Treehouse of Horror XIX
plot: The Simpsons' 19th Halloween Special, with parodies of "Transformers," "Mad Men," and "It's the Great Pumpkin, Charlie Brown."

title: Dangerous Curves
plot: The Simpsons take a Fourth of July vacation to a cabin hotel, which cause Homer and Marge to reminisce about two episodes from their past where they stayed in the cabin.

title: Homer and Lisa Exchange Cross Words
plot: Homer gets a job breaking up couples, and Lisa becomes an expert crossword puzzle solver, but Homer bets against her in a competition.

title: MyPods and Boomsticks
plot: Homer suspects that the family of Bart's new Muslim friend from Jordan is part of a terrorist plot, and Lisa becomes obsessed with her new MyPod.

title: The Burns and the Bees
plot: Lisa goes to extreme lengths to save Springfield's bees, only to have Mr Burns demolish her newfound sanctuary to build a stadium in an attempt to make himself, and his newly acquired basketball team more popular.

title: Lisa the Drama Queen
plot: Lisa and her new best friend create their own fantasy world, but Marge doesn't want Lisa to see her friend anymore after she finds out that they're too far gone in it.

title: Take My Life, Please
plot: Homer finds out that he actually won the senior class president election, and he gets an opportunity to find out how his life would have been different if it had happened.

title: How the Test Was Won
plot: Bart and his fellow underachievers are taken on a "field trip" to Capital City so that they can miss the standardized test, and Homer makes sure that nothing bad happens until their insurance goes back into effect.

title: No Loan Again, Naturally
plot: The Simpsons lose their house, but Flanders buys it and offers to rent it back to them. But when they turn out to be less-than-reliable renters, Flanders kicks them out.

title: Gone Maggie Gone
plot: In order to rescue Maggie from a Catholic orphanage, Lisa must solve a series of puzzles to reveal the identity of a gem that will bring peace to Springfield.

title: In the Name of the Grandfather
plot: The Simpsons take Grandpa to Ireland so he can go back to visit a pub he went to during the war, but Grandpa and Homer get suckered into buying the bar.

title: Wedding for Disaster
plot: Homer is kidnapped moments before he and Marge are supposed to re-renew their vows. However, Marge comes to the conclusion that Homer left her at the altar.

title: Eeny Teeny Maya Moe
plot: Moe begins dating a little person he met on the Internet, while Maggie is being bullied at the playground next to Moe's where Homer is leaving her.

title: The Good, the Sad and the Drugly
plot: Bart gets Milhouse to take the rap for a prank at school, and then blows him off when he falls for a cute 5th grade do-gooder, prompting Milhouse's wrath. Meanwhile, Lisa begins taking "happy pills" to improve her negative outlook.

title: Father Knows Worst
plot: Homer becomes a "helicopter parent" at Springfield Elementary by helping Bart finish a class project and helping Lisa become popular, and Marge finds a secret sauna in their house.

title: Waverly Hills, 9021-D'Oh
plot: The Simpsons set up a fake residence in Waverly Hills so that Bart and Lisa can attend school there.

title: Four Great Women and a Manicure
plot: Marge and Lisa tell stories inspired by three royal women: Queen Elizabeth I, Snow White, and Lady MacBeth. And one story about a man, Howard Roark, played by Maggie.

title: Coming to Homerica
plot: Townspeople build a wall around Springfield to keep "immigrants" from Ogdenville from relocating to their town.

title: Homer the Whopper
plot: A Hollywood studio makes a movie based on Comic Book Guy's comic book character "Everyman," and Homer is cast in the lead. However, Homer's weight fluctuations cause problems for the production.

title: Bart Gets a 'Z'
plot: When Bart's prank gets Ms. Krabappel fired from Springfield Elementary School, he tries to make it up to her without letting her know that he was responsible.

title: The Great Wife Hope
plot: Marge takes on the owner of an ultimate fighting league in the ring in order to get the sport banned in Springfield.

title: Treehouse of Horror XX
plot: Lisa becomes livid with Miss Hoover, and in a series of homages to classic Hitchcock sets out for deadly revenge. Next, Krusty's latest fast-food sandwich transforms news anchor Kent Brockman into an enraged zombie and twenty-eight days later, cannibal zombies have overrun Springfield. In the final frightening fable, Homer accidentally falls through a trapdoor in Moe's tavern and impales himself on the pipes of Moe's microbrewery. Moe serves the barflies a glass of delicious beer flavored with Homer's blood and Homer, now half-man, half-brewing apparatus, returns for vengeance.

title: The Devil Wears Nada
plot: Marge rediscovers her sexuality after appearing in a racy calendar, but Homer is too tired to respond to her advances because he is being worked to death by his new boss, Carl.

title: Pranks and Greens
plot: Bart meets the boy responsible for the greatest prank in Springfield Elementary School history, and discovers that he's now a 19-year-old loser. Meanwhile, Marge is scolded for providing unhealthy snacks for Maggie's play group.

title: Rednecks and Broomsticks
plot: Homer becomes an expert on moonshine when he starts hanging out with Cletus after he saves the Simpsons' lives, while Lisa becomes friends with three teenage Wiccans.

title: Oh Brother, Where Bart Thou?
plot: Bart becomes jealous of Maggie and Lisa's special bond as sisters, so he goes to an orphanage and "adopts" a little brother.

title: Thursdays with Abie
plot: Homer becomes jealous when a syndicated newspaper columnist begins publishing Grandpa's stories, while Bart is assigned to take care of the class's stuffed sheep for the weekend.

title: Once Upon a Time in Springfield
plot: The antagonism between Krusty and the new female co-star forced upon him soon turns to romance, while a headhunter encourages Homer, Lenny and Carl to take a job at another nuclear power plant.

title: Million Dollar Maybe
plot: Homer can't tell Marge he won the lottery because he was supposed to be giving a wedding toast when he bought the ticket. But Bart soon finds out where he's hiding the money and begins to blackmail him.

title: Boy Meets Curl
plot: Homer and Marge become members of the U.S. Olympic curling team. At the games, Lisa becomes addicted to collecting pins, and Bart tries to save her.

title: The Color Yellow
plot: While searching for an admirable ancestor for a class project, Lisa discovers the story of a relative named Eliza Simpson, who may or may not have helped a slave escape to freedom.

title: Postcards from the Wedge
plot: When Bart unsuccessfully tries to play Homer and Marge against each other, he comes up with a dangerous prank that is sure to get their attention.

title: Stealing First Base
plot: Bart gets Springfield Elementary School in legal trouble when he kisses the enigmatic daughter of two lawyers, while Lisa is depressed about being ostracized because she is smart.

title: The Greatest Story Ever D'ohed
plot: Ned takes the Simpsons on a pilgrimage to Israel in order to try and save Homer, but soon discovers that he may not be worth saving.

title: American History X-cellent
plot: Mr Burns is sent to prison for art theft, where a scary inmate introduces him to religion. Meanwhile Smithers becomes the boss at the plant, and Bart and Lisa try to share an ant farm.

title: Chief of Hearts
plot: Homer and Chief Wiggum's new friendship is put to the test when the chief becomes needy after being shot, while Marge suspects that Bart may be dealing drugs.

title: The Squirt and the Whale
plot: After a violent storm, Lisa tries to rally the townspeople and come to the rescue of a beached whale.

title: To Surveil, with Love
plot: Springfield covers the town with surveillance cameras after Homer creates a bomb scare at the train station. Meanwhile, Lisa considers becoming a brunette so that people will take her more seriously.

title: Moe Letter Blues
plot: Homer, Apu and Reverend Lovejoy all suspect that Moe may have left with one of their wives after receiving a mysterious letter, but which one is it?

title: The Bob Next Door
plot: Bart is convinced that the Simpsons' new friendly, unassuming neighbor is actually Sideshow Bob in disguise.

title: Judge Me Tender
plot: Moe's gruff and abrasive personality makes him the perfect hyper-critical judge, and lands him a spot on American Idol. Meanwhile, Homer makes Marge uncomfortable when he starts spending more time at home with Moe's now closed.

title: Elementary School Musical
plot: While Homer and Bart accompany Krusty to Oslo so he can receive the Nobel Peace Prize, Marge enrolls Lisa for a week in performing arts camp.

title: Loan-a Lisa
plot: Lisa uses the $50 she receives from Grandpa to give Nelson a microloan to jump-start his bicycle business, but soon comes to regret the decision.

title: MoneyBart
plot: Lisa takes over as manager of Bart's baseball team and uses statistical analysis to build a winner, but she takes all of the fun out of it and causes Bart to quit the team.

title: Treehouse of Horror XXI
plot: A Satanic board game causes other popular board games to come to life, Homer and Marge rescue a possible killer and let him on their boat, and a parody of "Twilight" where Lisa falls for a young vampire.

title: Lisa Simpson, This Isn't Your Life
plot: When Lisa discovers that Marge was also a model student, she tries to find out where everything changed so that she doesn't repeat her mistakes. Meanwhile, a series of chance accidents cause Bart to replace Nelson as school bully.

title: The Fool Monty
plot: After Mr. Burns finds out that he is dying, he has an accident and loses his memory, and all the townspeople use the situation to get their revenge on him.

title: How Munched Is That Birdie in the Window?
plot: Bart adopts a carrier pigeon, but Santa's Little Helper eats it.

title: The Fight Before Christmas
plot: Marge gets depressed when the rest of the family does not get into the holiday spirit, and she writes a letter, hoping to get some help; Mr. Burns and Moe's new friend delay the Simpsons as they attempt to travel to Hawaii for the holiday.

title: Donnie Fatso
plot: Homer goes to prison after attempting to get out of a series of fines with a bribe, but agrees to a reduced sentence by informing on Fat Tony for the FBI.

title: Moms I'd Like to Forget
plot: Bart sets out to uncover the origins of a sword-shaped scar on his hand; Marge reconnects with three friends she fell out with years ago.

title: Flaming Moe
plot: Moe tries to keep his 'straightness' a secret when he opens a gay bar; Skinner falls for a new teacher.

title: Homer the Father
plot: Homer picks up parenting advice from an 80s sitcom; Bart becomes involved in trading nuclear secrets.

title: The Blue and the Gray
plot: Moe employs Homer as his wing man, only to find Homer has more luck with the ladies than he does; Marge finds her first gray hair.

title: Angry Dad: The Movie
plot: Bart's "Angry Dad" character gets his own movie, but when the movie starts winning awards, Homer tries to hog all the credit.

title: The Scorpion's Tale
plot: Lisa's school project leads to the discovery of a new drug that makes the elderly less cranky and more tolerable.

title: A Midsummer's Nice Dreams
plot: After Tommy Chong walks away from the Cheech & Chong reunion tour, Homer goes on the road as his replacement. Meanwhile, Marge tries to help the cat lady with her hoarding problem.

title: Love Is a Many Strangled Thing
plot: The tables are turned for Homer and Bart after a therapist cures Homer of his violent tendencies toward the boy.

title: The Great Simpsina
plot: The family is greeted by folk singer Ewell Freestone when they visit a peach farm, but when Marge goes overboard with peach-inspired dishes, Lisa and Bart try to get rid of the unwanted fruit. Later, Lisa becomes a magician's apprentice to the legendary Great Raymondo who helps her develop her craft, but a schoolgirl crush clouds her judgment when she is coaxed into revealing the Great Raymondo's most famous magic trick to his phony archnemesis. But when the rival magician's act takes a risky turn, the Great Raymondo has one last trick up his sleeve and stages showdown with Ricky Jay, Penn & Teller and David Copperfield , showing them why he is the master of the craft.

title: The Real Housewives of Fat Tony
plot: Selma falls in love with and marries Fat Tony, and Lisa discovers that Bart has a skill for finding truffles.

title: Homer Scissorhands
plot: Homer opens his own salon after he discovers that he has skills as a hair stylist, and Lisa becomes suspicious after Millhouse gets a 5th grade girlfriend.

title: 500 Keys
plot: While Homer takes the Duff Blimp for a joyride, Lisa discovers a secret room in the basement of Sprinfield Elementary School.

title: The Ned-Liest Catch
plot: When Krabbapple gets suspended and put into detention after hurting Bart, Bart tries to break her out, but it ends that Flanders is the one that saves her life. But soon, Ned figures out that Edna has also dated other men such as Homer, Skinner Comic Book Guy and Aerosmith drummer Joey Kramer.

title: The Falcon and the D'Ohman
plot: Homer tries to befriend the new security guard at the nuclear power plant, who for some unknown reason isn't interested and keeps having flashbacks to his violent past as a government agent.

title: Bart Stops to Smell the Roosevelts
plot: Superintendant Chalmers gets fired after using unconventional methods to teach Bart and his friends about Teddy Roosevelt, so the boys take over Springfield Elementary until he gets his old job back.

title: Treehouse of Horror XXII
plot: Homer becomes paraplegic after a spider bite, Flanders becomes a vengeful killer after 'God' instructs him to kill the wicked, and Bart and Milhouse go undercover in an alien society.

title: Replaceable You
plot: Homer is betrayed by his new assistant at work and winds up working for her, and Bart and Martin create a science project that brings joy to the seniors at the Springfield Retirement Castle.

title: The Food Wife
plot: Homer is worried that he is no longer the cool parent after Marge, Bart, and Lisa become foodies.

title: The Book Job
plot: Homer and Bart put together a team to author the next successful tween novel franchise and make a million dollars, but discover that they need Lisa's help to pull it off.

title: The Man in the Blue Flannel Pants
plot: Homer gets promoted to accounts manager at the nuclear power plant, but soon learns the job robs you of your soul. Meanwhile, Lisa introduces Bart to "Little Women."

title: The Ten-Per-Cent Solution
plot: Krusty the Clown is stuck in a rut when the television network pulls his show from the air and his talent agency drops him as a client. But when the Simpsons introduce him to seasoned agent Annie, they are surprised to learn that Annie was Krusty's very first agent. Despite their rocky relationship, Annie is convinced to re-sign Krusty and craft his career comeback. But when Krusty's retro comedy show reboot is deemed a critical success, Krusty must decide to stay with his agent or side with the network executives.

title: Holidays of Future Passed
plot: Thirty years in the future the Simpsons get together for Christmas. Bart and Lisa are struggling as parents to connect with their children.

title: Politically Inept, with Homer Simpson
plot: Homer becomes the host of a popular political talk show, starts an "everyman" movement in Springfield, and ends up hand-picking Ted Nugent as the Republican nominee for president.

title: The D'oh-cial Network
plot: Lisa creates an online social network that becomes a Springfield obsession, but later becomes a victim of user backlash.

title: Moe Goes from Rags to Riches
plot: While Bart tries to regain Milhouse's friendship, Moe's bar cleaning rag tells his unlikely story of how he got to where he is today.

title: The Daughter Also Rises
plot: Lisa falls for an adventurous, Hemingway-esque young boy, while Bart and Millhouse set out to bust all the myths that surround Springfield Elementary School.

title: At Long Last Leave
plot: The town votes to kick the Simpsons out of Springfield, so they decide to move to the Outlands.

title: Exit Through the Kwik-E-Mart
plot: Bart becomes an urban vandal and decides to use Homer as his inspiration, while Apu hits hard times when a new trendy market takes all the Kwik-E-Mart customers.

title: How I Wet Your Mother
plot: The family break into Homer's dreams Inception-style after he begins wetting the bed.

title: Them, Robot
plot: Mr. Burns replaces all of the nuclear plant employees with robots--except for Homer, who stays along to supervise the robots and serve as a human scapegoat.

title: Beware My Cheating Bart
plot: Jimbo's girlfriend cheats on Jimbo with Bart, and Homer uses his new treadmill to catch up on a TV series about plane crash victims stranded on an island.

title: A Totally Fun Thing Bart Will Never Do Again
plot: Bart gets the family to take the cruise vacation of his dreams, and then launches a fiendish plot to ensure that it goes on forever.

title: The Spy Who Learned Me
plot: Homer uses his paid sick leave to improve his marriage, with the help of his imaginary friend, super-spy Stradivarius Cain. Meanwhile, Bart gets revenge on Nelson for stealing everyone's lunch money.

title: Ned 'N Edna's Blend Agenda
plot: After Ned and Edna announce publicly that they were secretly married, the two clash over how to raise Rod and Todd.

title: Lisa Goes Gaga
plot: After a desperate attempt by Lisa to become more popular backfires, Lady Gaga shows up in Springfield to help her with her self-esteem.

title: Moonshine River
plot: The Simpsons go back to New York City so that Bart can find his old girlfriend Mary Spuckler. Meanwhile, Lisa and Marge spend the trip trying to take in New York culture on the cheap.

title: Treehouse of Horror XXIII
plot: A black hole threatens to swallow Springfield, Homer tries to find the source of paranormal activity, and a "Back to the Future" parody in which Bart keeps Marge from marrying Homer.

title: Adventures in Baby-Getting
plot: Marge decides that she wants another baby, but Homer doesn't want one. Meanwhile, Bart tries to figure out where Lisa is secretly going after school.

title: Gone Abie Gone
plot: Homer invests Lisa's college fund on an online poker site. Meanwhile Abe disappears from the Springfield Retirement Castle.

title: Penny-Wiseguys
plot: Fat Tony has to serve jury duty, and his clerk, Dan, must run the mafia while he's gone. Meanwhile, Lisa considers making a disgusting change to her diet.

title: A Tree Grows in Springfield
plot: Homer becomes addicted to his new tablet computer. But when it is destroyed Homer becomes despondent, until he finds and provides hope for Springfield in the most unlikely place.

title: The Day the Earth Stood Cool
plot: Homer befriends a hipster and invites his family to move in next door. However, their friendship soon sours as Springfield is transformed into a haven for "coolness."

title: To Cur with Love
plot: When Homer shows no remorse over almost losing Santa's Little Helper, Grandpa tells everyone the story of Homer's childhood dog.

title: Homer Goes to Prep School
plot: Homer joins the "Springfield Preppers," an off-the-grid survivalist group whose leader has set up a top-secret retreat outside of town to prepare for the end of the world.

title: A Test Before Trying
plot: The fate of Springfield Elementary rests on Bart and his test scores, and Homer finds way to make money with his own parking meter.

title: Changing of the Guardian
plot: Homer and Marge find the perfect young couple and ask them to be the guardians for the kids in case something happens to them.

title: Love Is a Many Splintered Thing
plot: Mary Spuckler returns to Springfield and begins a relationship with Bart. However, Bart treats her with disrespect.

title: Hardly Kirk-ing
plot: Bart poses Millhouse as his father so that they can do adult activities, and Homer becomes skilled at finding lost objects thanks to Highlights magazine.

title: Gorgeous Grampa
plot: Homer's obsession with the TV show "Storage Battles" leads the family to discover Grampa's past identity as "Gorgeous Godfrey," the most feared, villainous man in pro-wrestling history

title: Black-Eyed, Please
plot: Ned gets fed up with Homer and punches him in the eye, and Lisa is a bullying victim from her new substitute teacher.

title: Dark Knight Court
plot: When Bart is accused of a prank he says he didn't commit, Lisa is forced to defend him in youth court, with former attorney general Janet Reno serving as judge.

title: What Animated Women Want
plot: Homer contemplates his next move after getting in the doghouse with Marge, while Millhouse's new Stanley Kowalski-inspired persona makes him suddenly attractive to Lisa.

title: Pulpit Friction
plot: Springfield gets a bedbug scare, the new assistant pastor at church appoints Homer as a deacon, and Marge loses her wedding dress.

title: Whiskey Business
plot: A new makeover could put Moe in a position to make big money, Bart fails at his job of taking care of Grandpa, and Lisa fights the shameless exploitation of Bleeding Gums Murphy's likeness.

title: The Fabulous Faker Boy
plot: Bart takes piano lessons from a cute Russian girl, Marge tries to teach the girl's father how to drive, and Homer loses the last of his hair.

title: The Saga of Carl
plot: Homer, Moe, Lenny and Carl win the lottery, but Carl steals the ticket and leaves with the money for Iceland.

title: Dangers on a Train
plot: When Marge tries to buy Homer snack cakes for their anniversary, she winds up meeting a married man who shares a common love of British television.

title: Homerland
plot: Homer returns from a nuclear power convention a changed man, and Lisa begins to suspect that he has become a domestic terrorist.

title: Treehouse of Horror XXIV
plot: The scariest Simpsons Halloween show yet, featuring an opening by Guillermo Del Toro.

title: Four Regrettings and a Funeral
plot: While attending a funeral, Homer, Marge, Mr. Burns, and Kent Brockman recall a past regret and try to find a way to rectify the situation.

title: YOLO
plot: Homer is stunned to learn he'll only live once. A pen pal from his youth helps him live that life to its fullest. Meanwhile Springfield Elementary institutes an honor code.

title: Labor Pains
plot: Homer helps take care of a child that he delivered in an elevator, and Lisa tries to organize the Springfield Atoms cheerleaders against the team's greedy owner.

title: The Kid Is All Right
plot: Lisa is distressed when she discovers that her new friend is a Republican, and they wind up running against each other as Springfield Elementary's second grade representative.

title: Yellow Subterfuge
plot: Principal Skinner promises the students that the best-behaved can take a ride in a submarine. Bart believes his past indiscretions will be forgotten. Lisa tries to help Krusty by suggesting him to sell the foreign rights to his shows.

title: White Christmas Blues
plot: When a sudden tourist spike means that the family cannot afford Christmas, the Simpsons open up their house to boarders.

title: Steal This Episode
plot: Fed up with the high price of Hollywood films, Homer begins screening pirated movies in his backyard, but is busted by the FBI after Marge turns him in.

title: Married to the Blob
plot: Comic Book Guy seeks romantic advice from Homer when he falls for a Japanese woman who's interested in manga.

title: Specs and the City
plot: Mr. Burns' Christmas present to his employees, a pair of augmented reality glasses, places a strain on Homer and Marge's relationship. Meanwhile, Bart wrestles with giving a Valentine's Day card to Nelson.

title: Diggs
plot: Bart becomes friends with a schoolmate who enjoys falconry, but turns out to be mentally disturbed.

title: The Man Who Grew Too Much
plot: Lisa becomes friends with Sideshow Bob, who now has a new job working with genetically-altered foods. Meanwhile, Marge becomes frustrated teaching abstinence for the church.

title: The Winter of His Content
plot: When Abe and two of his friends move in with the Simpsons after the Springfield Retirement Castle closes, Homer begins to embrace their lifestyle. Meanwhile, Nelson initiates Bart into the bully group after coming to his defense.

title: The War of Art
plot: The friendship between the Simpsons and the Van Houtens is challenged when a painting the Simpsons buy from the Van Houtens' yard sale is discovered to be extremely valuable.

title: You Don't Have to Live Like a Referee
plot: Homer becomes a referee for the World Cup and finds himself tested by bribers when the Simpsons travel to Brazil.

title: Luca$
plot: Marge becomes worried when Lisa starts dating a competitive eater-in-training, while Bart receives gifts from Snake Jailbird for helping him out.

title: Days of Future Future
plot: Thirty years into the future, Bart is having trouble dealing with his divorce, Lisa is struggling with her marriage to Milhouse, and Marge is finally fed up after burying yet another Homer clone.

title: What to Expect When Bart's Expecting
plot: Bart becomes a savior to Springfield couples trying to conceive when he inadvertently uses voodoo to get his art teacher pregnant.

title: Brick Like Me
plot: The Lego version of Homer begins to suspect that his entire Lego world is not real when a toy triggers a flashback to an alternate reality.

title: Pay Pal
plot: When Homer ruins his and Marge's chances of making a new couple friend, Marge decides to concentrate on finding a friend for Lisa. However, Lisa suddenly makes a new friend on her own.

title: The Yellow Badge of Cowardge
plot: Bart wins the annual "last day of school" race - with a little help from Nelson - and Homer attempts to bring back 4th of July fireworks, which have been canceled due to low budget cuts.

title: Clown in the Dumps
plot: Krusty has a crisis of conscience and retires from show business after his father dies before ever approving of his career. Meanwhile, Lisa becomes worried about Homer's health and life expectancy.

title: The Wreck of the Relationship
plot: Homer and Bart turn to the open seas to improve their relationship, and Marge becomes a trash talking victim after she drafts Homer's fantasy football team.

title: Super Franchise Me
plot: Marge opens a sandwich franchise store after her sandwiches become a huge hit at Springfield Elementary. But running day-to-day at the store proves challenging, especially when the same franchise opens another location across the street.

title: Treehouse of Horror XXV
plot: The 25th annual 'Simpsons' Halloween special includes an alternate dimension, a "Clockwork Orange"-style gang led by Moe and a visit from the Tracey Ullman-era Simpsons.

title: Opposites A-Frack
plot: An Assemblywoman brought in by Lisa to stop Mr. Burns' fracking operation ends up falling for him as much as he does for her.

title: Simpsorama
plot: The Simpsons meet the Planet Express crew, who have come to Springfield in the present to stop them from destroying the future.

title: Blazed and Confused
plot: Bart tricks his family into a camping trip at a strange event known as "Blazing Guy" so that he can get revenge on his sadistic new fourth grade teacher.

title: Covercraft
plot: Homer forms a cover band with other dads in town when he takes up bass guitar to deal with a mid-life crisis, but the band's modest success is soon overwhelmed by Apu's breakout potential.

title: I Won't Be Home for Christmas
plot: Marge kicks Homer out of the house for Christmas after he consoles Moe on Christmas Eve instead of going home.

title: The Man Who Came to Be Dinner
plot: An amusement park ride takes the Simpsons to the home planet of Kang and Kodos.

title: Bart's New Friend
plot: Homer is hypnotized into believing he's ten years old and ends up stuck in his new age when the hypnotist gets arrested, so he bonds with Bart and refuses to take back the responsibilities of adulthood.

title: The Musk Who Fell to Earth
plot: Inventor Elon Musk comes to Springfield, and Homer inspires him with a new idea that could revolutionize Springfield, but winds up costing Mr. Burns a ton of money.

title: Walking Big & Tall
plot: Marge tries to get Homer to lose weight. But instead, he finds a support group that encourages him to embrace his largeness.

title: My Fare Lady
plot: Marge gets a job as a driver for a transportation app service, while Moe is forced to work as a janitor at the nuclear plant after Homer causes the bar to go bankrupt.

title: The Princess Guide
plot: Moe falls in love with a Nigerian princess whose father is working out a uranium deal with Mr. Burns.

title: Sky Police
plot: The congregation, led by Marge, is forced to resort to gambling in order to collect money to fix the church, which Chief Wiggum destroyed with a jet pack he received by mistake.

title: Waiting for Duffman
plot: After "Duffman" retires, Homer wins a reality competition to become his replacement. But his contract states that he cannot drink beer, which gives him a new perspective on alcohol.

title: Peeping Mom
plot: Marge decides to follow Bart everywhere until he confesses to being involved in a bulldozer crash. Meanwhile, Homer ignores Santa's Little Helper when Ned gets a new dog.

title: The Kids Are All Fight
plot: The story of Bart and Lisa's rivalry is told when Homer finds an old film strip.

title: Let's Go Fly a Coot
plot: Bart takes up smoking e-cigarettes to impress Milhouse's cousin Annika while the rest of the family learns about Grampa's days in the Air Force.

title: Bull-E
plot: Bart gets bullied at a school dance, so Marge gets an anti-bullying law passed, which results in Homer being put in therapy for bullying Ned.

title: Mathlete's Feat
plot: Groundskeeper Willie becomes the coach of the mathletes, Lisa and other kids from Springfield Elementary compete against Waverly Hills Elementary.

title: Every Man's Dream
plot: Marge decides it's finally time to separate from Homer, and quickly moves on with her life. Homer is initially devastated, but soon stumbles into a romance with a younger woman.

title: 'Cue Detective
plot: A celebrity television chef challenges Homer to a barbecue cook-off. But before the competition, Homer's new, prized barbecue grill is stolen.

title: Puffless
plot: Patty and Selma try to quit smoking, but Patty moves in with the Simpsons when Selma takes it up again. Meanwhile, Maggie goes on an adventure with some local creatures.

title: Halloween of Horror
plot: The Simpsons are proud to be the most festively decorated house on the block. But when Lisa is traumatized at Krustyland Horror Night, she feels she cannot handle Halloween anymore.

title: Treehouse of Horror XXVI
plot: After killing Bart, Sideshow Bob doesn't know what to do with himself; Homer wakes up with short-term memory loss; Because of radiation, Lisa, Bart and Milhouse gain super-powers.

title: Friend with Benefit
plot: Lisa makes a new friend at school - Harper, who happens to be super-rich, while Homer makes friends with Harper's dad and sets out to continue living the good life when Lisa decides to end the friendship.

title: Lisa with an "S"
plot: Broadway legend Laney Fontaine transforms Lisa into a show-biz kid after Homer loses her chance at band camp.

title: Paths of Glory
plot: Lisa tries to restore the reputation of a forgotten Springfield female inventor, while Bart takes full advantage of his parents belief that he is a sociopath.

title: Barthood
plot: A tale of Bart's journey from youth to adulthood, where he is constantly in search of approval from his father and in the shadow of his more-successful younger sister.

title: The Girl Code
plot: When Homer loses his job due to Marge's social media post, he begins working as a dishwasher at a Greek restaurant. Meanwhile, Lisa creates an app that can predict the effect any post on social media will have.

title: Teenage Mutant Milk-Caused Hurdles
plot: Bart and Principal Skinner battle over the affection of Bart's new teacher, and a new milk-based product that Homer buys from the Kwik-E-Mart causes big changes in Bart and Lisa.

title: Much Apu About Something
plot: Apu's nephew makes big changes when he takes over the Kwik-E-Mart business, and Bart decides that he's through with being bad after his latest prank spirals out of control.

title: Love Is in the N2-O2-Ar-CO2-Ne-He-CH4
plot: Professor Frink's new invention turns him into a ladies' man, while a new pill at the Springfield Retirement Castle causes Grandpa to hallucinate back to his happiest moments.

title: Gal of Constant Sorrow
plot: Lisa tries to launch the career of a homeless Appalachian folk singer, but Bart warns her that she will just let her down. Meanwhile, Homer tries to rescue the cat, who is trapped in the walls of the house.

title: Lisa the Veterinarian
plot: Lisa takes a job as veterinarian's assistant, but soon lets the responsibilities of the job get to her head. Meanwhile, Marge decides to take a job as a crime scene cleaner.

title: The Marge-ian Chronicles
plot: Lisa signs up for an opportunity to be part of a mission to colonize Mars in ten years, and Homer's strategy to use reverse psychology to talk her out of it backfires.

title: The Burns Cage
plot: Homer tries to raise Smithers' spirits by finding him a man, and Lisa gets the lead in the school production of "Casablanca" alongside a new male student, sparking Millhouse's jealousy.

title: How Lisa Got Her Marge Back
plot: After Lisa overhears Marge say that she doesn't like Lisa's jazz music, Marge takes Lisa on a trip to Capitol City to regain her friendship. Meanwhile, Bart uses Maggie as his new partner in crime for his practical jokes.

title: Fland Canyon
plot: Maggie will not go to sleep, so Homer tells her a bedtime story about when the Simpsons and the Flanders went to the Grand Canyon together.

title: To Courier with Love
plot: After promising Marge the trip of a lifetime, Homer makes a deal with a travel agent to be a courier of a top-secret briefcase in exchange for a discounted family vacation to Paris.

title: Simprovised
plot: While trying to overcome a fear of public speaking, Homer creates an improv comedy troupe; Marge rebuilds Bart's treehouse.

title: Orange Is the New Yellow
plot: Marge lets Bart go to the park alone because he's too irritating, then she ends up getting arrested for leaving him unsupervised.

title: Monty Burns' Fleeing Circus
plot: Mr. Burns puts on a variety show at the Springfield Bowl.

title: Friends and Family
plot: Homer finds a new friend in a woman who acts just like him when Mr. Burns hires the other Simpsons as his live-in virtual reality family.

title: The Town
plot: Homer takes the family on a "hate-cation" to Boston after he catches Bart rooting for a rival football team.

title: Treehouse of Horror XXVII
plot: The children of Springfield fight to the death, Hunger Games style; Lisa's imaginary friend kills her real friends; Moe recruits Bart into his group of covert barfly agents.

title: Trust But Clarify
plot: Bart and Lisa investigate Krusty's new candy; Marge helps Homer dress for a promotion; Kent Brockman struggles with the changing media world.

title: There Will Be Buds
plot: Homer coaches the kids' lacrosse team with Kirk Van Houten, who disappears before the championship game, after Homer rants about him being a loser.

title: Havana Wild Weekend
plot: The Simpsons go to Cuba to get Grampa cheap medical care when the Retirement Castle and V.A. hospital are unable to solve his health problems.

title: Dad Behavior
plot: Homer discovers an app that makes his life easier, while Grampa learns that he'll be a father again.

title: The Last Traction Hero
plot: Homer is placed in a cast following a workplace accident, leading Marge to receive romance from an unexpected source; Lisa attempts to keep the peace as bus monitor.

title: The Nightmare After Krustmas
plot: Krusty and his daughter spend Christmas with the Simpsons; Reverend Lovejoy seeks converts to boost attendance at church; A Christmas toy scares Maggie.

title: Pork and Burns
